  • Reference

Glushko (1979), Lexically derived nonword set.

This data set gathered from table A2 includes a list of 52 lexically derived monosyllabic nonwords (26 pairs). Source words are either Regular or exception words.

g1979a2

Format

A data.frame with 52 rows and 5 variables:

set

Item set.

ortho

Orthographic representation.

phono

Phonological representation. Not included in original source.

rt_ms

Correct pronunciation latencies.

regularity

Spelling regularity bin: R (regular) or E (exception).

Source

Glushko, R. J. (1979). The organization and activation of orthographic knowledge in reading aloud. Journal of Experimental Psychology: Human Perception and Performance, 5(4), 674-691. doi:10.1037/0096-1523.5.4.674
